üß≠ Step 1: Update & Install Dependencies

Run the following commands:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install apache2 mysql-server php php-mysql libapache2-mod-php php-cli php-curl php-xml php-gd php-mbstring php-zip unzip wget curl -y


Enable Apache and MySQL:

sudo systemctl enable apache2
sudo systemctl enable mysql
sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl start mysql

üóÉÔ∏è Step 2: Create WordPress Database & User

Open MySQL shell:

sudo mysql


Then run:

CREATE DATABASE wordpress DEFAULT CHARACTER SET utf8 COLLATE utf8_general_ci;
CREATE USER 'wpuser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'StrongPassword123!';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON wordpress.* TO 'wpuser'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;


(Replace StrongPassword123! with a secure password.)

üìÇ Step 3: Download & Set Up WordPress

Create your custom directory:

sudo mkdir -p /var/ravinder/wp
cd /var/ravinder/wp


Download and extract WordPress:

wget https://wordpress.org/latest.tar.gz
tar -xvzf latest.tar.gz
sudo mv wordpress/* .
sudo rm -rf wordpress latest.tar.gz


Set permissions:

sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/ravinder/wp
sudo find /var/ravinder/wp/ -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
sudo find /var/ravinder/wp/ -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \;

‚öôÔ∏è Step 4: Configure Apache Virtual Host

Create a new Apache config file for your domain (replace yourdomain.com):

sudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/yourdomain.com.conf


Paste this:

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName yourdomain.com
    ServerAlias www.yourdomain.com
    DocumentRoot /var/ravinder/wp

    <Directory /var/ravinder/wp>
        AllowOverride All
        Require all granted
    </Directory>

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/yourdomain_error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/yourdomain_access.log combined
</VirtualHost>


Save and enable the site:

sudo a2ensite yourdomain.com.conf
sudo a2enmod rewrite
sudo systemctl reload apache2


Test config:

sudo apache2ctl configtest
sudo systemctl restart apache2

üåê Step 5: Map Your Domain

If using a real domain:

Go to your domain registrar (like GoDaddy, Namecheap, etc.).

Add an A record pointing to your server‚Äôs public IP address.
Example:

Name: @
Type: A
Value: <your_server_IP>
TTL: 3600


If using a test domain locally:

sudo nano /etc/hosts


Add line:

127.0.0.1   yourdomain.com

üîê Step 6: Install Free SSL (Let's Encrypt)

Install Certbot:

sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-apache -y


Run:

sudo certbot --apache -d yourdomain.com -d www.yourdomain.com


It will automatically configure HTTPS and redirect HTTP ‚Üí HTTPS.

üß© Step 7: Complete WordPress Installation

Now open your browser:

https://yourdomain.com


Then follow on-screen setup:

Site title

Username

Password

Database name: wordpress

Database user: wpuser

Password: StrongPassword123!

Host: localhost

üßº Step 8: Verify & Harden

Check if all is running:

sudo systemctl status apache2
sudo systemctl status mysql
